title: Ain't the Same
lyrics:
I'm too proud to say I'm sorry
Yeah we both crazy, let's be cautious
I think you blocked my number
Why the fuck you blocked my number?
Up all night, been hard to sleep, you won't talk to me

Can't get on my mind, know that I can't make it right if I see you

But I can't reach you, oh no

I can't remember the last time I saw your face

But I can remember the last time you felt this way

Last time I talked to you, you told me you needed space

Tryna be me without you, oh it just ain't the same



I'm too proud to say I'm sorry

But we both childish let's be honest, honest

That's why you blocked my number

Why the fuck did you blocked my number?



Up all night, been hard to sleep, you won't talk to me

Can't get you out my mind, know that I can't make it right if I see you

But I can't reach you, oh no

I can't remember the last time I saw your face

But I can remember the last time you felt this way

Last time I talked to you, you told me you needed space

Tryna be me without you, oh it just ain't the same



I'm over protective, you're too damn dismissive

Talkin' all that shit, you swore I'd never listen

Got the voice mail 'cause I ignored your message

Put some picture with some nigga there just to test me

Oh, oh, oh

Tryna be me without you, oh it just ain't the same
